metadata.name: Carve
metadata.description:
Urban Unconscious #1

The environment shapes us unconsciously in more ways than we care to admit and specifically architecture has been known to affect our psychological state, nature and behaviour.

'Urban Unconscious' is a body of photographic work based in the city of London which visually explores the interaction of life with urban architectural and geometrical structures, suggesting an interconnectedness in their momentary encounter. 

*Buyer will also receive a high quality 12” x 18” Giclee Print: https://www.chrisjjones.co/prints/p/carve
